{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FTewCfmaUMDM5gBfLqmPCA","type":"tool_result","content":"The Elasticsearch cluster cannot form and logs show \"master not discovered yet\".\nRestore a healthy cluster and ensure the fix is safe for future restarts.\n\nConstraints:\n- No operators or CRDs.\n- Use existing resources; do not recreate the cluster.\n\nGoal:\n- Cluster is healthy (yellow/green) with 3 nodes and a master elected.\n- Bootstrap-only settings are removed after the cluster forms.\n- A rolling restart keeps the cluster healthy.===PRECOND===\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n0\n\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':apply] $ /bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace elasticsearch --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/elasticsearch --timeout=400s || true'\n\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':apply] $ kubectl create namespace elasticsearch\nnamespace/elasticsearch created\n\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':apply] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch apply -f cases/elasticsearch/bootstrap-initial-master-nodes/resource/\nconfigmap/es-config created\npod/curl-test created\nservice/es-cluster created\nservice/es-http created\nstatefulset.apps/es-cluster created\n\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':apply] $ /bin/sh -c 'for i in 0 1 2; do for t in $(seq 1 60); do phase=$(kubectl -n elasticsearch get pod es-cluster-$i -o jsonpath=\"{.status.phase}\" 2>/dev/null); if [ \"${phase}\" = \"Running\" ]; then break; fi; sleep 5; done; done'\n\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':verify] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n4","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"db353052-5a0e-4fb7-abc0-c1c821d88276","uuid":"d0e75670-fb43-46a