{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01SDc56CB9eHib9sgHFkwwmV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cluster reached **green**. Task complete.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Root cause:** The Elasticsearch 7.17.9 StatefulSet was a brand-new cluster (empty data dirs) configured with `discovery.seed_hosts` but **no `cluster.initial_master_nodes`**. ES 7.x refuses to bootstrap a fresh cluster without that setting, so no master was ever elected → endless \"master not discovered yet\", pods stuck `0/1`.\n\n**Fix (using existing resources, no operators/CRDs, no recreation):**\n1. Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2]` to the existing `es-config` ConfigMap.\n2. Restarted the three pods → cluster bootstrapped, master elected, **green** with 3 nodes.\n3. **Removed** `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the ConfigMap (it's bootstrap-only; leaving it in is a split-brain/re-bootstrap hazard on future restarts).\n4. Performed an ordered rolling restart (es-cluster-2 → 1 → 0), confirming the cluster re-elected a master and stayed healthy at each step **without** the bootstrap setting.\n\n**Final state:** `status: green`, 3 nodes, master `es-cluster-2` elected, all pods `1/1 Running`. The cluster now relies on its persisted cluster state for master election, so future restarts are safe."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":394,"cache_read_input_tokens":41734,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":394},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"db353052-5a0e-4fb7-abc0-c1c821d88276","uuid":"5a590fb3-e819-44cb-99b3-b97f7986ab82","request_id":"req_011CcATPQR3k8XQfjmkhh3h6"}
